# DashCam – Colour & Style Consistency

Always use CSS variables from `src/styles.css`. Never hardcode hex, oklch, or arbitrary Tailwind colour classes.

## Brand tokens
- Yellow: `var(--dashcam-yellow)` → Tailwind: `text-primary`, `bg-primary`
- Black: `var(--dashcam-black)` → Tailwind: `bg-background`, `text-primary-foreground`

## Semantic tokens (prefer Tailwind class)

| Token | Tailwind class |
|-------|----------------|
| --background | bg-background |
| --foreground | text-foreground |
| --card | bg-card |
| --border | border-border |
| --muted-foreground | text-muted-foreground |
| --destructive | bg-destructive / text-destructive |
| --accent | bg-accent / text-accent-foreground |
| --secondary | bg-secondary / text-secondary-foreground |
| --ring | ring / outline-ring |

## Fonts
- Body: `font-sans` (Manrope)
- Brand headings: `font-brand` (Orbitron)

## CLAUDE.md checklist (review before every change)
- Responsive UI, minimal styling
- No changes outside scope — ask first
- Split files >200 lines into components
- No unrequested functionality
- Show only changed code, never the full file
- Include file path comment at the top of every code block
